BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 30 Apr (MENA)--A military court has sentenced 
'Abd-al-Sattar Abu-Husayn, a journalist for AL-SHA'B, mouthpiece 
of the opposition Labor Party, to one year in prison and fined 
him 500 pounds for publishing news related to the Armed Forces 
without prior permission. 
  The journalist can appeal for commutation or cancellation of 
the sentence or for a retrial. If the ruling is confirmed, a 
petition for a reconsideration of the sentence can be made to 
the military appeals office within 15 days from the date the 
convict is notified of the confirmation. 

